RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 1 5F Turf CR: 86. Maiden Special Weight Purse 82000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In The Last 3 Starts Preferred). (Rail at 30 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DARK VINTAGE (IRE) was nudged from the gate and gained a tracking position towards the rail, was shoved on momentarily then had to pause before easing out to advance past the quarter pole, bumped with SHARPAZANO when collaring that one in upper stretch, moved to command with a furlong remaining, kicked clear under left handed asks and held firm. MURPHY BOY hopped at the break then steadied soon after, regrouped and advanced while saving ground into the turn, continued progress past the five sixteenths, came out for the drive and closed nicely between rivals to nab the place in the final yards. OSAGE CREEK , away alertly, prompted the pace three wide outside the leader, shifted wider with hard pursuit into the lane and kept on with effort. SHARPAZANO sped clear early, set the pace towards the rail, drifted out a bit when engaged in upper stretch and bumped with the winner, corrected to battle past mid stretch then gave way grudgingly in the final yards. RASTAMAN VIBE , forced in at the break, recovered and raced in the clear early, advanced four wide approaching the stretch, shifted out a bit but came up empty late. CRONE ZONE , keyed up pre race and ran off with his rider a bit, bore out at the break, dropped off the pace, saved ground nearing the lane and failed to menace'. ZISKEY (IRE) broke slowly, lagged off the pace saving ground and was outrun. EISENHOWER veered in at the break bothering foes, raced a bit green while off the rail into the turn, chased between rivals nearing the stretch and tired. THE RACE WAS HAND TIMED

RACE.FOOTNOTES: IMPERIAL HORNET , urged from the gate, took command inside rivals leaving the four and a half furlong marker, handled outside pressure from three foes, spurted clear approaching the stretch, widened under solid handling in mid stretch, wandered outward a bit leaving the sixteenth pole, was soon straightened and held sway while kept alert. COACH CRONIN broke slowly, recovered and gained towards the rail in the opening three sixteenths, dropped back as the leading quartet widen from him leaving the far turn, swung out six wide for the drive and came back on to nip FORDY G for the show. FORDY G , with the pace four wide, disputed the issue four deep exiting the far turn, remained four wide with pursuit into the stretch, stayed willingly past the sixteenth pole then faded late. AUSTONIAN broke outward and bumped with SANGER, moved up and bid two wide between runners, vied around the turn, failed to keep pace heading to the stretch and retreated. MY MAN FLEURY , brushed early, was rated back from between runners in the opening furlong, dropped off the pace and failed to respond.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CALI BAY (IRE) rated forwardly off the rail, dropped in some with pursuit past the three furlong marker, crept closer with the riderless OVERRULE to his outside entering the lane, responded and forged through to the inside of BATTLE CALL leaving the furlong grounds, wrested command past the sixteenth pole and held firm under a drive. BATTLE CALL , jostled and steadied at the break, rushed up three to four wide and moved to command near the half mile marker, dropped in some and was driven well clear past the three eighths, remained clear off the inside in mid stretch, dug in after being headed and kept on gamely. STORMY VICTORY , forced in at the break by the riderless OVERRULE, was brushed soon after, rated back and guided towards the rail, came out near the three eighths, pursued between runners past the five sixteenths, shifted out wider for the drive and closed steadily. BROTHER REID , bumped leaving the gate, saved ground, eased out and moved between foes nearing the lane, altered out in upper stretch and churned on. TABLE FOR TWO , taken to rate four wide early, drafted back off the pace, swung six wide for the drive and came up empty. LIMITED HEATWAVE cleared early and set a rated pace towards the rail, was overtaken nearing the half, stayed on to pursue leaving the far turn then tired nearing the lane. THIRSTY PAPPY , bumped and steadied at the break, failed to menace. RELAXED ARTIST (IRE) , off a bit awkwardly, raced three wide early and gave way. OVERRULE was acting up just prior to the start, reared while in the hands of the assistant starter and unseated his rider. Following a stewards' inquiry, OVERRULE was declared a non-starter. The race was HAND TIMED.
